The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bangla coach suspended 

Singapore: Bangladeshs Argentine coach Diego Cruciani has been suspended for two matches after attempting to assault an Indian referee during his teams 2007 Asian Cup pre-qualifying match against Pakistan. 

The punishment was handed down by the Asian Football Confederation (AFC), on the recommendation of Fifa. 

It will affect Bangladeshs Group F Asian Cup qualifiers against Uzbekistan on February 22 and Hong Kong on March 1, the AFC said on its website. 

 Haq, a Delhi-based Fifa referee, is a regular official of the National Football League and all major tournaments of India. (AFP) 




